<plot>"Leap Year Nightmare" is a documentary about at-risk teens shooting their first short film. Julie Alexander, a director at the Rhubard Theater, works with 11 teens to write, direct, and act out their short film. A professional film crew comes for one weekend to mentor the teens on being cast and crew for their film, and a documentary filmmaker captures it all on tape. Crew members continually switch hats to act as both cast and crew as tempers flare, personalities collide, and the clock ticks.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?327747</url></doc>
